<HL>
   Comstock Begins Public Offer
</HL>
<DATE>
05/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C19
</SO>
<CO>
   CMRE
</CO>
<IN>
STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)
</IN>
<LP>
   DALLAS -- Comstock Resources Inc. said it commenced a
public offering of 2.5 million of common shares for $5.75
each.
   The company said proceeds will be used to repay part of
its $9.8 million in bank debt, continue development of 95 oil
and gas wells near Amarillo, Texas, and acquire additional
oil and gas properties.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Eppler, Guerin &amp; Turner Inc., Dallas, is managing the
underwriting.
</TEXT>
